tourism %>%
  features(Trips, feat_stl) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = trend_strength, y = seasonal_strength_year,
             col = Purpose)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(vars(State))

tourism %>%
  features(Trips, feat_stl) %>%
  filter(
    seasonal_strength_year == max(seasonal_strength_year)
  ) %>%
  left_join(tourism, by = c("State", "Region", "Purpose")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Quarter, y = Trips)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_grid(vars(State, Region, Purpose))

library(broom)
library(glue)

tourism_features <- tourism %>%
    features(Trips, feature_set(pkgs = "feasts"))
## Warning: `n_flat_spots()` was deprecated in feasts 0.1.5.
## Please use `longest_flat_spot()` instead.
## Warning: 304 errors (1 unique) encountered for feature 6
## [304] The `urca` package must be installed to use this functionality. It can be installed with install.packages("urca")
## Warning: 304 errors (1 unique) encountered for feature 7
## [304] The `urca` package must be installed to use this functionality. It can be installed with install.packages("urca")
## Warning: 304 errors (1 unique) encountered for feature 8
## [304] The `urca` package must be installed to use this functionality. It can be installed with install.packages("urca")
## Warning: 304 errors (1 unique) encountered for feature 20
## [304] The `fracdiff` package must be installed to use this functionality. It can be installed with install.packages("fracdiff")
pcs <- tourism_features %>%
    select(-State, -Region, -Purpose) %>%
    prcomp(scale = TRUE) %>%
    augment(tourism_features)

pcs %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = .fittedPC1, y = .fittedPC2, col = Purpose)) +
    geom_point() +
    theme(aspect.ratio = 1)

outliers <- pcs %>%
  filter(.fittedPC1 > 10) %>%
  select(Region, State, Purpose, .fittedPC1, .fittedPC2)

outliers
## # A tibble: 4 x 5
##   Region                 State             Purpose .fittedPC1 .fittedPC2
##   <chr>                  <chr>             <chr>        <dbl>      <dbl>
## 1 Australia's South West Western Australia Holiday       10.4      -1.93
## 2 Great Ocean Road       Victoria          Holiday       11.3       3.69
## 3 Snowy Mountains        New South Wales   Holiday       10.3       4.27
## 4 South Coast            New South Wales   Holiday       14.1       4.19
outliers %>%
    left_join(tourism, by = c("State", "Region", "Purpose")) %>%
    mutate(Series = glue("{State}", "{Region}", "{Purpose}", .sep = "\n\n")) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = Quarter, y = Trips)) +
    geom_line() +
    facet_grid(Series ~ ., scales = "free") +
    labs(title = "Outlying time series in PC space")
